reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great organizer folders, and tough, too!,
reviews.reviewText: I am trying hard to organize my paperwork. These binder pockets are great for that. For example, earlier I just stuck a bunch of auto service and insurance records in a binder because hole punching all those individual pieces of paper was a daunting, time intensive task. With these organizers, their deep pockets and 3 ring binder holes, I could fit everything in neatly to sit on shelf in less than 10 minutes. And to find and take out what I want, I don't have to undo the rings and fight to get other pages to stay put or get back on the rings. I can look through pockets easily. These plastic organizers are not only colorful, but so much thicker and tougher than paper ones I've tried in the past whose binder holes inevitably rip. I will be getting more of these for household records and warranties.

reviews.reviewText: These are sturdy and colorful folders, good for school or office work. The only unusual thing about them is that they're shorter than the average folder. If you put regular notebook type papers in them, the top of the paper would be even with the top of this folder. It would still work fine, but your papers might be a little more protected with the taller type of folder.
